  <p><a href="/shermangallery">View gallery</a></p>  
  <img src="/static/img/sherman.jpg" class="img-circle" alt="Cindy Sherman" width="250" height="310" align="right"> 
  <p class="description">
    A portraitist who “depersonalizes” her portraits, Cindy Sherman portrays the superficial facade that covers one’s true identity - made ghostly - in her overuse of makeup. In addition to covering each subject’s face with an abundance of makeup, Sherman further dispossess the subjects of identity by leaving all of her works untitled. Interestingly, Sherman herself is the subject of her own photographs. However, it is deliberate that she looks completely different in each of her photographs. With this Gothic approach to art, she raises a concern for women as media, that dictates what constitutes the “ideal woman,” grows in influence.
  </p>

